\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Chapter 5: Lust\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\fs36 \cf0 ME\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 The internet is an incredible tool. It's a $100 billion+ industry... just the part we don't talk about.\
The impact of the digital age and what it has done to us and for us... it has connected us, given us access to information, and provided entertainment on a scale we've never seen. That's a good thing.\
Sexuality, in and of itself, is a good thing. It's a gift from God, designed for intimacy, connection, procreation, and joy. It's awesome!\
But there is a problem... a deeper, below-the-surface alligator underneath the beautiful, curated feeds and the endless stream of content. It\'92s the distortion of the gift.\
They have a vested interest in keeping you and your eyes glued to that screen... and it is working.\
Look up the stats on how much time the average person spends consuming sexually explicit content... it's staggering... and it's damaging us.\
Researchers have known for years what this kind of access does. When participants in studies are exposed to a constant stream of "perfect" bodies and consequence-free sexual encounters, their levels of satisfaction with their real-life partners drop almost immediately. Their brains are rewired. The difference wasn\'92t more connection\'97it was less. Less intimacy. Less humanity. What they discovered scientifically is what Scripture\'92s been telling us for thousands of years: lust eats away at your soul.\
TRANSITION: How can a harmless glance, scrolling through certain feeds, looking at images, or even just a private fantasy have any damaging affect on us?\
There are a lot of reasons, but for today's purpose... it feeds into an alligator we all have in our lives. The alligator of lust.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 DEFINING LUST\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 Virtue
\f1\b0  - Love / Devotion 
\f0\b Definition
\f1\b0  - Resenting a person's humanity by desiring their body for your own gratification.
\f0\b What we say
\f1\b0  - "I have to have it." / "I need that." / "I deserve this." 
\f0\b Object of desire
\f1\b0  - What you can 
\f2\i take
\f1\i0  (a body, a feeling, a fantasy) 
\f0\b Root Emotion
\f1\b0  - Emptiness, craving, entitlement (PAUSE when you feel this emotion) 
\f0\b Spiritual Lie
\f1\b0  - This person is an object for my pleasure. 
\f0\b FACES - Behaviors
\f1\b0  - Secrecy, isolation, objectification, consumption, comparison 
\f0\b False Aim
\f1\b0  - To find satisfaction or fulfillment 
\f0\b Blocked Good
\f1\b0  - True intimacy and connection 
\f0\b Catalyst
\f1\b0  - Objectification\
That last one - objectification... that's the catalyst that starts the whole process. When we objectify, it starts us down a path of feeding something that will eventually consume us.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 Catalyst of Objectification\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 WHY? Objectification is the thief of intimacy! Objectification is the soil lust thrives in. The internet has monetized it. Advertising has weaponized it. Culture has normalized it.\
Illustration of me walking through the airport. I remember a time I was walking to my gate, and I was bored. I started "people watching," but it wasn't that. I was scanning, rating, judging. I wasn't seeing 
\f2\i people
\f1\i0 ; I was seeing 
\f2\i parts
\f1\i0 . A woman walked by, and in my mind, I reduced her entire being\'97her story, her soul, her dignity\'97to a single "look." I started to consume, not connect. All of a sudden I was face to face with something dark in my heart that could destroy my peace and, if allowed to grow, destroy my relationship with my wife and my God.\
Thankfully, I know how to deal with this one... we'll talk about that a little later...\
TRANSITION: You're probably not tempted in that exact same way... honestly, we all have our own triggers... but... you are tempted when...\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

