\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 GOD\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 David and Bathsheba
\f1\b0 \
If you're not familiar with it, that's ok. It's the story of one of the greatest kings in history. It starts in 2 Samuel 11. It's not the second sin... but it's one of the most important.\
It's "the time when kings go off to war." But David... "remained in Jerusalem." Mistake #1: He was idle. He wasn't where he was supposed to be.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 11:2 One evening David got up from his bed and walked around on the roof of the palace. From the roof he 
\f0\b saw
\f1\b0  a woman bathing. The woman was very beautiful,\
\ls3\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 3 and David 
\f0\b sent
\f1\b0  someone to find out about her. The man said, \'93She is Bathsheba, the daughter of Eliam and the wife of Uriah the Hittite.\'94\
\ls3\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 4 Then David 
\f0\b sent
\f1\b0  messengers to 
\f0\b get
\f1\b0  her. She came to him, and he 
\f0\b slept
\f1\b0  with her.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 He saw. He desired. He 
\f2\i took
\f1\i0 .\
He didn't ask the right questions. He should have asked, "How do I honor God right now?" "How do I protect this woman's dignity and her husband's honor?" Instead, he was upset... that she was married. But not so upset that it stopped him.\
Lust didn't stay a "thought." It grew. It grew from a 
\f2\i look
\f1\i0 ... to 
\f2\i inquiry
\f1\i0 ... to 
\f2\i adultery
\f1\i0 ... to 
\f2\i deception
\f1\i0 ... to 
\f2\i murder
\f1\i0 .\
How was sleeping with Bathsheba supposed to help David? It did nothing for his relationship with God, for the woman he violated, for the soldier he would soon murder, or for his family. So what is going on? Lust. It's what lust does in our hearts and souls. Instead of David looking inward to his own heart and his commitment to God... he looked outward and consumed everything in a moment of selfish desire. Inwardly in David's heart was an alligator that was growing... REMEMBER what we said earlier... 
\f0\b Definition
\f1\b0  - Resenting a person's humanity by desiring their body for your own gratification. 
\f0\b Spiritual Lie
\f1\b0  - This person is an object for my pleasure.\
David could have fixed and focused on himself... it was easier to take the woman. A man after God's own heart... destroyed a family, murdered a loyal friend, and broke his connection with God... all because a "small" sin was allowed to grow.\
